The paper discusses privacy-enhancing technologies (PETs) and their implementation in system design, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cyber security (cs.CY). The paper also discusses technical building blocks and design strategies, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper mentions the need for a data governance strategy, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves managing and analyzing large amounts of data.
